    For the trust claim: RESPOND to the naive fiduciary rebuttal. Acknowledge
    that fiduciary relationships can be exploited. Argue that the solution is
    STRUCTURAL SAFEGUARDS: user-auditable memory logs, user-editable memory,
    separation of user-facing and operator-facing data, third-party memory
    auditors. These safeguards exist for human fiduciaries (financial auditors,
    medical boards) and can be stronger for AI (because memory is digital and
    inspectable). Address revealed vs reflective preferences: memory should
    store CORRECTIONS (user explicitly overrides agent behavior), not just
    behavioral patterns.

  ⊨ argument takes a clear FOR position
