⊢= obs-dialectic-convergence
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "DIALECTIC CONVERGES VIA ALTERNATING REFINEMENT: the ⊢∘ loop alternated which side got refined — FOR, AGAINST, FOR, then fixpoint. Each refinement directly addressed the other side's strongest point. FOR's fiduciary claim was attacked by AGAINST's 'naive fiduciary' rebuttal, then FOR responded with structural safeguards. This is thesis-antithesis-synthesis: each round produces a STRONGER version of both positions by forcing engagement with the best counterargument."

⊢= obs-fixpoint-meaning
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "FIXPOINT IS NOT AGREEMENT — IT'S EXHAUSTION OF EASY IMPROVEMENTS: both sides scored 8/8 but they DISAGREE. The FOR side says 'auditable memory is safe.' The AGAINST side says 'information asymmetry is inherently dangerous.' These are different value commitments, not resolvable by argument refinement. The ⊢∘ loop detected this: improved=false because both sides reached high quality, not because they converged on the same answer. Dialectic fixpoint ≠ consensus."

⊢= obs-asymmetric-evolution
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "ONLY THE WEAKER SIDE EVOLVES EACH ROUND: this is ESSENTIAL for convergence. If both sides refined simultaneously, they'd drift without engaging each other. By refining only the loser, the debate becomes a RESPONSE CHAIN: each refinement responds to the winning argument's strongest point. The winning side's argument is frozen, becoming the target. This is why the scores oscillated (FOR won, then AGAINST won, then FOR won) instead of both climbing together."

⊢= obs-dual-cell-evolution
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "⊢∘ OVER TWO CELLS IS NEW: program 02 evolved one cell (summarize). This program evolves TWO cells (argue-for, argue-against) through the same loop. The ⊢∘ harden(argue-for, argue-against) means both are subject to rewriting, but only one changes per round. This is adversarial co-evolution: each cell improves in response to the other. The ⊢∘ combinator handles this naturally — it doesn't care how many cells are evolving."

⊢= obs-debate-produces-knowledge
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "THE DEBATE PRODUCED NOVEL INSIGHTS NEITHER SIDE STARTED WITH: 'fiduciary trust' didn't appear in v0 arguments. 'Information asymmetry as structural precondition' didn't exist in v0. 'Corrections over patterns' was synthesized in response to 'revealed vs reflective preferences.' The judge's feedback created these — by identifying specific weaknesses, it forced each side to generate NEW arguments, not just restate old ones. The ⊢∘ loop is a knowledge generator, not just a quality optimizer."

⊢= obs-judge-as-curriculum
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "THE JUDGE IS A CURRICULUM DESIGNER: each round's feedback is a specific lesson. Round 0: 'distinguish welcome vs unwelcome memory.' Round 1: 'fiduciary framing is naive — argue info asymmetry.' Round 2: 'respond to naive fiduciary with structural safeguards.' Each lesson builds on the previous round's arguments. The judge doesn't just score — it identifies the MOST PRODUCTIVE direction for improvement. This is curriculum learning via adversarial pressure."
